cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use EpiNet, please cite it as below."
title: "EpiNet: the Epistemic Network toolkit — transparent network and feature-space analysis with honest evaluation and federated contestability"
abstract: >-
  EpiNet is a research/education toolkit for graph-shaped datasets. It computes
  graph features, evaluates an outcome model with discrimination and calibration
  metrics, a label-permutation null, and community-aware splitting, scores how
  contestable each nearest-centroid call is (closed-form flip-distance), and
  reconstructs its standardization and contestability spine from per-site
  aggregates behind a fail-closed governance gate. It is a demonstrator, not
  clinical decision support.
type: software
